body:
Adds support for most expressions (even `$c`!) in event controls, with the exception of function calls.

If the expression is 'complex' (basically not just a varref or select with constants), it's stored in a temporary variable, to avoid recalculating it multiple times per trigger eval call. This results in code like this:
```cpp
__Vtrigcurr = <expr>;
__Vtriggered.at(<[changed] trigger>) = __Vtrigcurr != __Vtrigprev;
__Vtriggered.at(<posedge trigger>) = __Vtrigcurr & ~__Vtrigprev;
__Vtriggered.at(<negedge trigger>) = ~__Vtrigcurr & __Vtrigprev;
__Vtrigprev = __Vtrigcurr;
```

This PR is against `develop-v5`, as it has better support for `[changed]` senitems. Also, the PR affects senitem term construction code which is completely different on `develop-v5`.

Signed-off-by: Krzysztof Bieganski <kbieganski@antmicro.com>
